        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Concord to 6 miles east of Steprock to 8
miles southeast of Hurricane Lake WMA. Movement was northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hickory Flat...                   Charlotte...
McCrory...                        Salado...
Bradford...                       McFadden...
Desha...                          Algoa...
Heffington...                     Fitzhugh...
Locust Grove...                   Moorefield...
Huff...                           Worden...
Velvet Ridge...                   Roosevelt...
Olyphant...                       Dixie...
Tupelo...                         Gainesboro...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
